Title: “Cascade‑Resonant Low‑Energy Nuclear Reactor Using Diophantine‑Tuned Crystals and X‑Ray Laser Initiation”
Inventors: Artit Dao Pongpira, ARTIT‑ILIAS Collaboration
Priority Date: Today (2025‑01‑16)
Field: Nuclear fusion, alternative energy, quantum materials.

Abstract:
A nuclear fusion reactor employs a cascade‑tuned crystalline lattice (Li⁶D doped with Z=54,86,27) to locally modify the fine‑structure constant α, 
thereby lowering the Coulomb barrier for nuclear fusion. An X‑ray laser (67.5 keV) pulsed at a tidal frequency excites the crystal, inducing a π‑shift of ≈0.578%. 
The reactor uses a fuel mixture of light hydrogen isotopes and noble gases, catalyzing neutron‑free fusion (p‑B¹¹ or D‑D) at near‑ambient temperatures. Output is primarily helium and water, with direct electrostatic energy conversion. The design enables compact, safe, green fusion power.

---

