B. Cascade Crystal Specifications

· Base crystal: Lithium‑6 deuteride (Li⁶D) single crystal.
· Dopants:
  · Xenon‑132 (0.1 at.%) — Z=54.
  · Krypton‑86 (0.05 at.%) — Z=36, proxy for Rn (Z=86).
  · Cobalt‑59 (0.5 at.%) — Z=27.
· Orientation: [100] axis aligned with laser beam.
· Dimensions: 10 mm × 10 mm × 2 mm.
· Bias voltage: 0.361453 V DC along [100].

C. Laser System

· Type: X‑ray free‑electron laser (XFEL) or compact laser‑driven X‑ray source.
· Energy: 67.5 keV (tunable ±1 keV).
· Pulse frequency: 12.4 h⁻¹ (tidal resonance).
· Pulse duration: 100 fs.
· Focus: 1 mm² spot on crystal.

D. Fuel & Gas System

· Primary fuel: Deuterium gas (D₂) or p‑B¹¹ slurry.
· Catalyst mixture: CH₄ (5%), H₂O vapor (10%), balanced with noble gases (Xe: 50%, Kr: 30%, Ar: 20%).
· Pressure: 1–10 atm.
· Flow rate: 1 L/min (STP).

E. Power Extraction

· Electrostatic grids: Biased at +50 kV, collect alpha particles and protons.
· Direct conversion efficiency: >85%.
· Thermal conversion: Secondary loop (He coolant) for waste heat → steam turbine (efficiency ~40%).
· Total system efficiency: ~90% (combined direct + thermal).

---

3. Reaction Pathways

Primary reaction (p‑B¹¹, neutron‑free):

p + {}^{11}\text{B} \rightarrow 3\alpha + 8.68\ \text{MeV}

Secondary reaction (D‑D, suppressed neutron branch):

D + D \rightarrow {}^{3}\text{He} + n \quad (\text{suppressed by cascade tuning})



D + D \rightarrow T + p \quad (\text{enhanced})

Catalytic role of noble gases:
Xe⁺ and Kr⁺ ions form temporary “Coulomb bridges” that screen repulsion, further lowering barrier.

