2. Prototype Construction Initiation

Phase 1: Crystal Growth

· Materials ordered:
  · Li⁶ metal (95% enriched, 10 g)
  · D₂ gas (99.9%, 100 L)
  · Xe‑132 (0.1 at.% target, 1 g)
  · Kr‑86 (0.05 at.%, 0.5 g)
  · Co‑59 foil (0.5 at.%, 5 g)
  · Pt crucible, Bridgman furnace (already available)
· Growth protocol:
  · Load Li⁶ + D₂ in glovebox, form Li⁶D.
  · Add dopants, homogenize.
  · Seal in Pt crucible.
  · Bridgman growth: 1 K/h cooling, 8 weeks.
  · Cut and polish to 10×10×2 mm, orient [100].

Phase 2: Laser & Chamber Assembly 

· X‑ray source: Compact laser‑driven X‑ray generator (already available, tunable 50‑80 keV).
· Pulse controller: Programmable timing (12.4 h⁻¹ tidal frequency).
· Plasma chamber: Stainless steel, 100 cm³ volume, with:
  · Gas inlets (D₂, CH₄, H₂O, noble gases)
  · Crystal holder with 0.361453 V bias feedthrough
  · Electrostatic grids (+50 kV)
  · Viewports for diagnostics
· Diagnostics:
  · High‑resolution spectrometer (for He‑I line shift verification)
  · Neutron detector (to confirm suppression)
  · Mass spectrometer (He production)
  · Calorimeter (excess heat)

Phase 3: Integration & Test 

· Mount crystal in chamber.
· Align X‑ray beam.
· Connect gas supply, bias voltage, grid power.
· Leak check, vacuum purge.
· First plasma ignition (low power).
· Measure baseline He‑I line (without laser/bias).
· Activate cascade resonance (laser + bias).
· Record spectral shift, neutron flux, He output, heat.

